title: T.H MASARYK "The spirit of Russia" (1913)
description:
FIST PUBLISHED IN GERMAN IN ----1913----- AS "RUSSLAND UND EUROPA"


    London translation 1919


------------------------------------------------------------------


    Masaryk studied in Wien and was  a Herr Professor in the Prague University.
    Later , he became the first president of the (Versailles) Czech Republic 



-------------------------------------------------------------------

    The book:

    The part one (volume 1) is by far the most interesting: 213 pages of interpre-
    tative history of Russia , as seen from The 1913 Habsburg empire.

    Part two is more damaged by the time passed: a cultural history of Russia.

    Part three discusses the inquietudes born out of the 1905 revolution:

    "Houston ,  i have a bad feeling".
